# TRND_FLWR Automation

- Prefer `npm run verify` before committing or opening PRs. It runs lint, app/server builds, and automation type-checking.
- Use `npm run cursor:review` for local read-only review of the current branch.
- Use `npm run cursor:ship` for the full cloud-agent shipping loop after local verification.
- Cursor cloud automation requires `CURSOR_API_KEY`; do not commit real API keys or Firebase service account JSON.
- Keep source-ingest changes focused on real data behavior: no fake source records, generated stories, or placeholder market signals.
- For PRs, branch from the active work branch and avoid force-pushing unless the user explicitly approves it.
